## Test Anti-Pattern Audit

**Summary: 3 Critical · 1 High · 2 Medium · 2 Low** — This class is the likely root cause of your incident. Half the tests can never fail.

---

### 🔴 Critical — False Confidence

**1. `GetUser_NonExistentId_ReturnsNull` — No assertion**

The comment `// should be null` replaced an actual assertion. This test always passes.

```csharp
// BEFORE
var user = repo.GetById(999);
// should be null

// FIX
var user = repo.GetById(999);
Assert.IsNull(user);
```

**2. `AddUser_DuplicateId_ThrowsException` — Swallowed exception**

If `Add` stops throwing, the test silently passes — the method falls through with no `Assert.Fail()` on the non-throwing path.

```csharp
// FIX — replace entire method body
var repo = new UserRepository();
repo.Add(new User(1, "Alice"));
Assert.ThrowsException<InvalidOperationException>(() => repo.Add(new User(1, "Bob")));
```

**3. `DeleteUser_RemovesFromRepository` — Always-true assertion**

`Assert.AreEqual(repo.Count, repo.Count)` compares the value to itself. This can never fail.

```csharp
// BEFORE
Assert.AreEqual(repo.Count, repo.Count);

// FIX
Assert.AreEqual(0, repo.Count);
```

---

### 🟠 High

**4. `AddUser_NullUser_ThrowsArgumentNullException` — Broad exception type**

Method name says `ThrowsArgumentNullException` but asserts `ThrowsException<Exception>`. Any exception satisfies this — including an unrelated `NullReferenceException` from a bug.

```csharp
// BEFORE
Assert.ThrowsException<Exception>(() => repo.Add(null!));

// FIX
Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(() => repo.Add(null!));
```

---

### 🟡 Medium / 🔵 Low

| Severity | Test | Anti-Pattern | Fix |
|----------|------|-------------|-----|
| Medium | `GetUser_ExistingId_ReturnsUser` | Weak assertion — only checks `IsNotNull`, never verifies `Id` or `Name` | Add `Assert.AreEqual("Alice", user.Name)` |
| Medium | `UpdateUser_ChangesName` | Negated assertion — `!= "Alice"` passes even if name becomes garbage | Change to `Assert.AreEqual("Alicia", user.Name)` |
| Low | Class-level | Unused static `HttpClient _client` — never referenced, `IDisposable` never disposed | Remove it |
| Low | `SearchUsers_ByPartialName` | Leftover `Console.WriteLine` debugging | Remove it |

---

### ✅ Positive Observations

- **`GetAllUsers_ReturnsCorrectCount`** is well-written — checks count and verifies each member.
- **Naming convention** is consistent `Method_Scenario_Expected` throughout.
- **Good test isolation** — each test creates its own `UserRepository` instance.
- **AAA structure** is clear and tests are concise.

---

### Priority

Fix the **3 Critical** issues first — those are your "tests passing but verifying nothing" problem. The High and Medium fixes are quick one-line changes you can do in the same PR.
